The paper deals with the analysis of performance of MIMO communication systems employing spatial multiplexing and zero-forcing detection, which falls under the domain of information theory and communication systems (cs.IT and cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the effects of interference and channel statistics on performance, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.MA).
